args:
With Ranzal and Louise turned into children
and Mercury in human form, the trio infiltrate
the Emile Academy, where thrilling espionage,
white-hot combat, and unexpected romance
await them!
The new teacher is SUPER pretty!
And she's a dragon too!\n...Ah! Here she comes!
Quiet down now, children. I'd like to\nintroduce a pair of new transfer students.
Heya, guys! Nice to meetcha!\nCan I get a ＂hot diggity dog＂ up in here?
Hello. I'm Louise. If I had to say what I'm\nbest at, it would be housework. I like\ntaking care of people whenever I can.
I can get a little overprotective, but\nthat's something I'm working on.\nIt's nice to meet you all!
Please give them a warm welcome, class.\nNow, if you two would find your seats...
We've made it inside, at least.
Yeah. Now comes the hard part.
Right. We need to perform reconnaissance \non the academy. But how to go about it?
Ryu. One of your classmates...\nthough that ends today.
Because I love you. From today on,\nI hope not to be your classmate, but\nyour boyfriend.
*whistle* Nice goin', Louise!\nYou little man-eater, you.
This isn't a laughing matter! Er, how do I...
I... I'm terribly sorry, but while I respect\nyour feelings, I cannot return them in kind.
We only just met. We know nothing at all\nabout one another. Surely you understand?
Look at you, getting all serious with a kid.

Just because you're speaking to a child
doesn't mean you should take them
lightly. As an adult, it's my responsibility
to act with sincerity.
Fair enough. You're definitely the pro\nhere when it comes to raisin' rugrats.
You may not know me, but I\nalready know all about you!
My sixth sense told me everything.\nI know you're like a big sister!
You're in the same grade as me, but you're\noverflowing with gentle acceptance! With\ngenerous care! You're not the average girl!

You could read me stories and tuck me
under the covers at night! You could tell
me everything's okay when I'm scared!
PLEASE TAKE CARE OF ME!
Truly, these feelings must be love!
Mrgh! Something to SAY, new kid?\nAre you trying to insult my love?
Naw, it's not that. It's just... Y'know.
Yes, I believe I DO know!\nYou love her too, don't you?!
And THAT'S why you feel so threatened by\nmy love! I see you now for what you are:\nnot a classmate, but a bitter rival!
Didja stretch before you reached, bud?\nSomebody put this brat down for a nap\nalready!
Hmph. Lash out all you want. We shall see\nwhich of us is the more deserving match\nfor sweet Louise.
I challenge you to a duel, new kid!
And so the opening bell rang out on their white-hot\nbattle of love, its sound echoing across campus!
Yeah, I'm pretty sure that's just the class\nbell...
We will hold an outdoor mock combat trial\ntoday. You children will one day shoulder\nthe Empire's future. Give it your all!
A combat simulation as part of their\nnormal curriculum...
Isn't it a bit much, asking these children\nto face imperial soldiers and fiends?
I'm all for teaching runts to fend for\n'emselves, the world bein' what it is these\ndays, but yeah, this is a touch hardcore.
Perhaps this means these students are\nbeing trained specifically for the military.
But it's not like they've got 'em swingin'\nweapons around non-stop. The lectures\nwere normal. Just boring classroom—
Have at you, Dummy McTransferpants!\nThe time has come to settle which of us\nis worthy of Louise's affections.
Whoever slays the most fiends during the\ncombat simulation wins!
Not that you need bother trying. Your love\nCLEARLY pales in comparison to mine!
You little... If that's what you want, FINE! A\ngrown man never turns his back on a fight!
Time to teach you some manners.\nNow GET BACK HERE!
Wai—Ranzal! ...And there he goes. *sigh*\nHe's as much a child as his little friend.
At this rate, I question what chance we\nhave of gathering any intel at all before\nour bodies revert.
Sooooo, which team are you on, Louise?
Aw, don't be shy! You know what I mean.\nRanzal or Ryu! Which one do you like?!
I'm definitely Team Ryu.\nHe's smart AND super cute!
I'm all-in on Team Ranzal! You just\nKNOW he's gonna grow up to be a hunk!
Ooh, I can TOTALLY see it! I bet even\nhis muscles are gonna have muscles!
(Is...that what folks are into these days?)
I'm so jealous, Louise. You get to be all,\n＂Boys, please! Don't fight for my sake!＂
Right?! It's like we're smack in the middle\nof a schoolyard soap opera or something!
(Ugh, but if we don't find some decent\nintel and get out of here soon, this'll turn\ninto an adult-sized problem in a hurry...)
Oh, right. We've got Chairman Emile's\nlecture next.
Emile?! He comes to campus himself?!
(He might drop his guard around a child\nand let something slip. It's the perfect\nchance to pump him for information!)
I've got my sights set on you, Emile.
Wait. Louise, are you...\nAre you Team Chairman?!
Heh heh heh... Soon. SOON I shall make\nmy glorious appearance! Stay tuned, kids.
